
TO INSTALL:

cd ~
git clone http://github.com/jbe/.vim.git
ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc
cd ~/.vim
vim +BundleInstall +q


FEATURES

* My opinions

* Syntax support
  - Markdown (and markdown-preview)
  - CoffeeScript
  - Slim templates
  - ANSI escaped files

* Integration
  - Git (fugitive.vim)
  - Jekyll blogging (jekyll.vim)
  - Hithub gists (gist.vim)

* Useful plugins
  - FuzzyFinder
  - NERDTree
  - Taglist
  - Tagbar
  - Align
  - Tab completion (snipmate.vim)
  - ConqueShell


REQUIREMENTS

Exuberant ctags (for taglist)
$ sudo apt-get install ctags



TIPS

Have a look at the key bindings in vimrc for some inspiration.

Do :BundleInstall! to update the plugins at any time :)
